Each method essentially transforms the continuous PDE into a large system of linear or nonlinear algebraic equations, which can then be solved using computer algorithms like iterative solvers (e.g., Jacobi, Gauss-Seidel, Conjugate Gradient) or direct solvers (e.g., LU decomposition). The choice of method depends on the specific problem, geometry, and accuracy requirements.
